{
  "stem": "1736.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Belgrade was, of course, the opposite situation.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Belgrade was Serb.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it's something that's reflected in today's politics.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Hated the Germans.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Couldn't even-- we weren't allowed to speak the German language, because we might have been taken as German nationals.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that was difficult.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were there, living under fairly difficult circumstances for a few days.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the transport then went on to cross the border into Greece.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On another train.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We went to Greece.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a very short train.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were told-- or not us personally, but the-- the people leaving, you know, we heard through them that the Germans were coming in to Greece from the south and that we had to get out quickly, to get out the place.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in order to facilitate the train going faster, they disconnected the last wagon, which contained our worldly possessions.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now, we had been given in Zagreb a small suitcase with clothing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were putting our things in there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so we lost all that again.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the train sped off across the border into Turkey, across the Bosphorus, came to Istanbul.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "About 100.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "About 100.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And just with the possessions you had on you.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's it.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And Istanbul, again, we stayed for two or three days.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, there was no danger there anymore, just--",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She was with us, yeah.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then we continued by train right through Turkey, Syria, where we-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Syria, Lebanon.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think we were in Aleppo.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And later in April, it was Pesach '41.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we arrived in Israel, the-- the Palestinian border after that, only to be told, where are your papers?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Your-- and they told-- explained the situation, that we were escapees and all this.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And anyway, the British said, no, that's not an order.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
